# Part 1 — Hero Epilogue + Gradient Transition

## 1a. Extend hero pin: `+=400%` → `+=600%`

**File:** `src/components/sections/Hero/HeroSection.jsx`

Change `end: '+=400%'` to `end: '+=600%'`.

Split the raw ScrollTrigger progress (0→1) into two independent values:

| Raw range | Derived value | Drives |
|---|---|---|
| 0 → 0.667 | `frameProgress = clamp(rawP / 0.667, 0, 1)` | Canvas frames 0→274 |
| 0.667 → 1.0 | `epilogueProgress = clamp((rawP − 0.667) / 0.333, 0, 1)` | Text reveals + gradient |

Update `onUpdate`:
```js
const raw = self.progress
const frameP = Math.min(1, raw / (2/3))
const epilogueP = Math.min(1, Math.max(0, (raw - 2/3) / (1/3)))
useHeroProgress.setState({ progress: frameP, epilogueProgress: epilogueP })
canvasApiRef.current?.setProgress(frameP)
if (gradientRef.current) gradientRef.current.style.opacity = String(Math.min(1, Math.max(0, (epilogueP - 0.3) / 0.55)))
```

Also add `gradientRef` to the JSX alongside a new `EpilogueCopy` component.

## 1b. Add `epilogueProgress` to Zustand store

**File:** `src/store/useHeroProgress.js`

Add `epilogueProgress: 0` to initial state.

## 1c. New `EpilogueCopy.jsx`

**File:** `src/components/sections/Hero/EpilogueCopy.jsx`

Subscribes to `epilogueProgress`. Three placeholder lines, each fade+translateY driven by scroll:

| Line | Text | Fade-in threshold |
|---|---|---|
| 1 | `WHERE SILENCE MEETS THE SKY` | ep 0.05–0.20 |
| 2 | `YOUR JOURNEY BEGINS` | ep 0.25–0.40 |
| 3 | `ABOVE THE ORDINARY` | ep 0.45–0.60 |

Pure inline-style mutations (no re-renders), same pattern as `HeroCopy.jsx`.

